which comes from Wiener desynchronises people (something like good old greek sophists saying "everyone has his/her Truth") though cybernetics formerly tried to unify everything, what I guess you're trying to do too , - what is the aim behind finding a general theory, beyond unifying and controlling systems ? You say it is the goal of your work, isn't there another goal between that (something like Power, we could think then that you try to get people lost into an architecture instead of writing a book, which is too easily criticizable)?- cybernetics have failed as trying to think society with homeostasis , social homeostasis must not be a goal (it must for those who want to master the elements of the system - here, the people...). Cybernetics must not be applied to social relations, cybernetics are a science for controlling elements.<p>Have you heard about Simondon ? he has, I believe, a general theory, and something called "Universal Cybernetics", but I am not expert enough to explain. I have understood that he has given another Theory of Information with the concept of "metastability", what is involved in a cell separation : things contain their becoming, or something like that.<p>Good luck, anyway, I will come back because it's intereting.</nodetxt><p><p><p><HR WIDTH=420><font size=-1><a href="/COPYR.html">Copyright&copy; 2000 Principia Cybernetica</a> - <a href="REFERPCP.html">Referencing this page</a></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=140 BGCOLOR=DED6A5><TABLE WIDTH=100% CELLPADDING=15 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 BGCOLOR=#EEEEEE><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP>      <BR>   <B> <FONT FACE="ARIAL, HELVETICA, SANS-SERIF" SIZE=-1>Author</FONT></B><br>  <FONT SIZE=-1> <author>Le Roux Ronan (<a href=mailto:rlrbroadcast [ at ] voila.fr>rlrbroadcast[at]voila.fr</a>) </author></FONT><p>   <B> <FONT FACE="ARIAL, HELVETICA, SANS-SERIF" SIZE=-1>Date</FONT></B>   <BR><FONT SIZE=-1><update> Jun 16, 2000</update> </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>